The elective course is intended for 5th year students of medicine. The course deals with the subspecialities of plastic and reconstructive surgery; indications for and methods of operation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim is to introduce classical reconstructive surgery, hand and microsurgery, surgical treatment of burn injuries, aesthetic surgery.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student knows 1) the concept, content and history of plastic surgery; 2) subdivision of plastic surgery and its areas of usage;  3) types of wounds, wound healing; 4) treatment methods used in plastic surgery;  5) relying on gained knowledge the student is able to solve different problems concerning the surgery of skin and soft tissue.
